Based on the provided evidence, the presented UTAUT2 model variation was accepted in this structure and, consequently, subjected to further stages of analysis. Based on the modified UTAUT2 model, eight hypotheses were formed, each one related to a specific predictor describing the effect on a dependent variable (behavioral intention). The mentioned hypotheses are listed in Table 1. Hierarchical linear regression was used to examine the impact of variables at different levels of the hierarchy on the outcome (dependent) variable and to observe unique contributions of the variables in the hierarchical structure of the data. Based on the model summary (Table 5), it can be concluded that the model was able to explain 65% of the variance (R2 = 0.65).
