Table 6 provides information on model coefficients and data for hypotheses testing. There is enough evidence to support five out of the eight proposed hypotheses. This demonstrates significant, direct, and positive effects of performance expectancy, social influence, hedonic motivation, habit, and personal innovativeness on the behavioral intention to use ChatGPT. The remaining three hypotheses that argue that effort expectancy, facilitating conditions, and price value have significant, direct, and positive effect on behavioral intention were not supported and, thus, rejected (a summary is presented in Table 7).
